Linda M. Tharby 

		
		EVP and Chief Human Resources Officer, 

	
		 Becton, Dickinson and Company 	

 
Last Updated: 10/11/2016 



Executive Summary
Linda Tharby has served as the Executive Vice President and Chief Human Resources Officer at Becton, Dickinson and Company since October 2016. She joined the Company in 1996 and was named General Manager, Canada by the year 2000. In 2008, she was named Worldwide President for Diabetes Care and in 2013, was appointed Group President, Pr 
Personal Attributes and Interests

She was honored as 2012 Woman of the Year by the Northern New Jersey and Rockland County Chapter of the Juvenile Diabetes Research Foundation for her extensive work with diabetes care throughout her career.

Current Focus

Barricor Technology: In August 2016, commenting on Barricor technology, Tharby told analysts, “If you think about blood collection, we created a blood collection tube with our gel about 25-plus years ago. So, this 
Key Challenges

Increasing Gender Diversity: Tharby was a key player in forming the Women’s Leadership Network of BD. She said in an interview, "BD has been involved with healthcare for over 100 years and as healthcare is ev 
Biographical Highlights

Tharby was born on August 18th in Sault Sainte Marie, Ontario.
She holds a BBA from Wilfrid Laurier University (1986-1990). 
Other Boards and Organizations

Member, Board of Overseers, Mailman School of Public Health, Columbia University

 





